        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 1 at 6:11PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 610 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
northeastern Lake Jackson, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Jackson, southern Angleton, Freeport, Clute, Surfside Beach,
Richwood, Brazoria, Jones Creek, and Oyster Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
